column3: I believe the issue was that this `print` did nothing, because by default `flush=False` (see https://docs.python.org/3.8/library/functions.html#print ).\n\nTesting locally and on travis x86, it did always happen to print, just not on travis arm.
`CI_WAIT` no longer exists and this should be a no-op
Yes, `CI_WAIT` was dropped from the `.travis.yml` in #18929.
